messages.msgSnippet: In a message dated 06/08/2000 2:01:58 PM Pacific Daylight Time, Jaam1224@cs.com writes:
messages.messageBody:
In a message dated 06/08/2000 2:01:58 PM Pacific Daylight Time,
Jaam1224@... writes:

<<
Has anyone ever had a nursing photo taken? I am dying to do this but I am
afraid they are going to be really expensive. I would love to hear your
thoughts. >>

Yes I have had a portrait done at
a La Leche League conference. If you are in So Cal you can contact the lady
that does these. They were wonderful and reasonable (I think $55 for 8 4x6
prints). A couple of the pics were just us posing together and one of naked
baby, no parts exposed LOL. If you aren't in the area I would say contact
LLL International to find a local group or see if they have someone to refer
you too. I would't feel comfortable with just anyone taking these pics thats
for sure, as I was half naked myself (underware and a denim shirt open,
baby naked...very nice, she covers you up so that you aren't hanging all out
or stretch marks exposed etc!)

Kathy

messages.subject: Re: [Unschooling-dotcom] pictures
messages.msgSnippet: My aunt took a picture of me nursing dd#1 7 years ago .I think I ll ask her for a copy of it. She has a liver melanoma and is slowly being taken away from us.
messages.messageBody:
My aunt took a picture of me nursing dd#1 7 years ago .I think I'll ask her
for a copy of it. She has a liver melanoma and is slowly being taken away
from us. This is one precious belongings she has that I'd like to get. Not
because I'm selfish, but because to this day I vividly remember the moment
she took it and it means a lot to me.
Amy
